Description:
An updated automated processing method for obtaining layer dip from Greenland and Antarctic radio-echo sounding (RES) data. The algorithms are presented in MATLAB, which is the standard in this field. Algorithms are robust, applicable, and can be used to process large (several terabyte) ground and airborne RES datasets. 

The algorithms essentially comprises six basic steps: 
(1) Noise reduction; 
(2) Layer identification; 
(3) Isolating individual layers objects; 
(4) Measuring dip and associated properties; 
(5) Error reduction;
(6) Collation dip measurements.

